cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.MM, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the integration of different services and technologies to provide seamless connectivity in fifth-generation wireless communication networks, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper evaluates the interplay between access and backhaul and the resulting end-to-end user rates, which involves the study of information transmission and processing.
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper focuses on the performance of massive MIMO self-backhauling for ultra-dense small cell deployments, which is a topic related to communications and networking.
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the impact of different SCs deployment strategies on the end-to-end user rates, which involves the study of multimedia content delivery and quality of service.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper analyzes the impact of time resource allocation between radio access and backhaul links, which involves the study of system dynamics and control.
